mith commissioned in the Air Force in December 2009 as a 2nd Lieutenant and was stationed as an Aircraft Maintenance Officer at Little Rock AFB  Little Rock  AR  He served in the 19th Equipment Maintenance Squadron and 19th Aircraft Maintenance Squadron  during which time he was requested on 3 occasions to serve as the Airman Leadership School CGO Mentor in addition to serving as the CGOC President  He was selected to deploy as the C 130 Maintenance Unit OIC to Bagram  Afghanistan in the summer of 2013 in support of Operation Enduring Freedom during which time his unit surpassed every flying record in existence there  Captain Smith was selected to serve as an ROTC instructor at Virginia Military Institute  Detachment 880 in November 2013 and has remained there since  EDUCATION 2005 Bachelor of Science Aerospace Studies Minors Professional Communications  Psychology  International Relations  Space Studies 2013 Masters of Aeronautical Science Space Operations concentration ASSIGNMENTS 1  Jan 2010   Nov 2010  Aerospace Ground Equipment Officer In Charge  19th EMS  Little Rock AFB  AR 2  Nov 2010   Nov 2011  Maintenance Flight Officer In Charge  19th EMS  Little Rock AFB  AR 3  Nov 2011   Nov 2012  J model Aircraft Maintenance Unit Assistant Officer In Charge  Little Rock AFB  AR 4  Nov 2012   Mar 2013  H E model Aircraft Maintenance Unit Assistant Officer In Charge  Little Rock AFB  AR 5  Apr 2013   Sep 2013  C 130 Expeditionary Aircraft Maintenance Unit Officer In Charge  Bagram Airfield  Afghanistan  Operation Enduring Freedom 6  Nov 2013   Present  Assistant Operations Officer  Virginia Military Institute  Detachment 880  Lexington  VA MAJOR AWARDS AND DECORATIONS Air Force Achievement Medal with oak leaf cluster Afghanistan Campaign Medal NATO Medal PROFESSIONAL MEMBERSHIPS AND AFFILIATIONS Air Force Association Military Officers Association of America EFFECTIVE DATES OF PROMOTION  Second Lieutenant December 17  2009 First Lieutenant December 17  2011 Captain Decem